### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a web framework (e.g., Flask).
- Handles routing for all nine pages, user session management, and business logic.
- Reads from and writes to the local text files in the 'data' directory for data persistence.
- Implements all required functionalities such as enrollment, progress tracking, assignment submission, certificate generation, and profile updates.

data/
- Directory containing all local text files used for data storage as specified.
- users.txt, courses.txt, enrollments.txt, assignments.txt, submissions.txt, certificates.txt store respective data in the defined formats.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each of the nine pages.
- Each template corresponds to a page described in the requirements, with elements identified by the specified IDs.
- Templates use templating syntax to dynamically render user-specific and course-specific data.

static/
- Contains static assets such as CSS and JavaScript files.
- css/styles.css for styling the web pages.
- js/scripts.js for client-side interactivity and UI behavior (e.g., button actions, form validations).

This structure keeps the backend logic consolidated in a single Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity, fully aligning with the project requirements.
